textAfterTable: File Format Description Template file created by various types of applications; saves the default settings for the page layout, written text, and other information for a document; used for generating documents with a similar style and structure. Example uses of template files include company letterhead templates and drawing templates. Program(s) that open .TPL files Windows Open with the original program that created the template Mac OS Open with the original program that created the template Updated 7/14/2011 Add Info Need to open a .TPL file? Try File Viewer for Windows.
